I'm not hungry.

227
00:19:42.139 --> 00:19:44.642
You want me to starve.

228
00:19:44.725 --> 00:19:49.563
An old man like me,
who hardly has strength as it is.

229
00:19:49.647 --> 00:19:53.484
Me, to whom you owe your very life!

230
00:19:53.567 --> 00:19:55.611
Don't be silly.

231
00:19:59.365 --> 00:20:02.410
See? Scrumptious.

232
00:20:10.960 --> 00:20:14.922
Did anyone think to dredge the lake?

233
00:20:15.005 --> 00:20:16.966
This morning.

234
00:20:19.135 --> 00:20:22.513
- Hear that?
- What?

235
00:20:24.557 --> 00:20:25.683
Zero!

236
00:20:40.865 --> 00:20:42.825
Where have you been?

237
00:20:42.908 --> 00:20:46.412
Call a town meeting
and I'll tell everyone all about it.

238
00:20:46.495 --> 00:20:49.290
- When?
- Immediately!

239
00:20:53.461 --> 00:20:56.297
Town meeting!

240
00:20:56.380 --> 00:20:59.258
Town meeting!

241
00:20:59.341 --> 00:21:02.011
Town meeting tonight!

242
00:21:03.929 --> 00:21:06.307
Town meeting!

243
00:21:06.390 --> 00:21:08.601
Town meeting tonight!

244
00:21:26.660 --> 00:21:28.120
Listen, everyone.

245
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:33.876
I want to tell you about Christmas Town.

246
00:21:36.921 --> 00:21:40.424
<i>There were objects so peculiar</i>
<i>They were not to be believed

247
00:21:40.508 --> 00:21:43.594
<i>All around, things to tantalize my brain

248
00:21:43.677 --> 00:21:47.515
<i>It's a world unlike anything</i>
<i>I've ever seen

249
00:21:47.598 --> 00:21:51.018
<i>And as hard as I tried</i>
<i>I can't seem to describe

250
00:21:51.101 --> 00:21:54.396
<i>Like a most improbable dream

251
00:21:54.480 --> 00:21:58.025
<i>But you must believe</i>
<i>when I tell you this

252
00:21:58.108 --> 00:22:03.239
<i>It's as real as my skull</i>
<i>and it does exist

253
00:22:03.322 --> 00:22:05.783
Here, let me show you.

254
00:22:10.746 --> 00:22:13.165
<i>This is a thing called a present

255
00:22:13.249 --> 00:22:16.168
<i>- The whole thing starts with a box</i>
<i>- A box?

256
00:22:16.252 --> 00:22:17.837
<i>- Is it steel?</i>
<i>- Are there locks?

257
00:22:17.920 --> 00:22:21.423
<i>- Is it filled with a pox?</i>
<i>- How delightful, a pox

258
00:22:21.507 --> 00:22:22.716
If you please.

259
00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:25.594
<i>Just a box with bright colored paper

260
00:22:25.678 --> 00:22:28.097
<i>And the whole thing's</i>
<i>topped with a bow

261
00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:31.183
<i>- A bow?</i>
<i>- But why? How ugly! What's in it?

262
00:22:31.267 --> 00:22:33.269
<i>That's the point of the thing</i>
<i>Not to know

263
00:22:33.352 --> 00:22:36.063
<i>- It's a bat! It's a rat!</i>
<i>- Will it bend? Will it break?

264
00:22:36.146 --> 00:22:38.732
<i>Perhaps it's the head</i>
<i>I found in the lake

265
00:22:38.816 --> 00:22:41.402
<i>Listen now</i>
<i>You don't understand

266
00:22:41.485 --> 00:22:44.989
<i>That's not the point</i>
<i>of Christmas land

267
00:22:45.072 --> 00:22:49.118
Now, pay attention.
<i>We pick up an oversized sock

268
00:22:49.201 --> 00:22:51.620
<i>And hang it like this on the wall

269
00:22:51.704 --> 00:22:54.999
<i>- Oh, yes, does it still have a foot?</i>
<i>- Let me see, let me look

270
00:22:55.082 --> 00:22:58.544
<i>- Is it rotted and covered with gook?</i>
- Let me explain.

271
00:22:58.627 --> 00:23:03.674
<i>There's no foot inside, but candy</i>
<i>Or sometimes it's filled with small toys

272
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:06.635
<i>- Small toys? Do they snap?</i>
<i>- Or explode in the sack?

273
00:23:06.719 --> 00:23:09.471
<i>Perhaps they spring out</i>
<i>and scare girls and boys

274
00:23:09.555 --> 00:23:12.016
<i>What a splendid idea</i>
<i>This Christmas sounds fun

275
00:23:12.099 --> 00:23:14.727
<i>I fully endorse it</i>
<i>Let's try it at once

276
00:23:14.810 --> 00:23:17.271
<i>Everyone, please</i>
<i>Now, not so fast

277
00:23:17.354 --> 00:23:20.608
<i>There's something here</i>
<i>that you don't quite grasp

278
00:23:23.110 --> 00:23:26.363
Well, I may as well give them
what they want.

279
00:23:26.447 --> 00:23:29.992
<i>And the best I must confess</i>
<i>I have saved for the last

280
00:23:30.075 --> 00:23:33.412
<i>For the ruler of this Christmas land

281
00:23:33.495 --> 00:23:37.082
<i>Is a fearsome king</i>
<i>with a deep mighty voice

282
00:23:37.166 --> 00:23:40.419
<i>Least that's what</i>
<i>I've come to understand

283
00:23:40.502 --> 00:23:44.006
<i>And I've also heard it told</i>
<i>that he's something to behold

284
00:23:44.089 --> 00:23:47.468
<i>Like a lobster, huge and red

285
00:23:47.551 --> 00:23:51.055
<i>When he sets out to sleigh</i>
<i>with his rain gear on

286
00:23:51.138 --> 00:23:54.683
<i>Carting bulging sacks</i>
<i>with his big great arms

287
00:23:54.767 --> 00:23:58.062
<i>That is so, I've heard it said

288
00:23:58.145 --> 00:24:01.607
<i>And on a dark cold night</i>
<i>under full moonlight

289
00:24:01.690 --> 00:24:06.779
<i>He flies into a fog</i>
<i>like a vulture in the sky

290
00:24:07.488 --> 00:24:10.824
<i>And they call him

291
00:24:10.908 --> 00:24:14.536
<i>Sandy Claws

292
00:24:19.625 --> 00:24:24.964
<i>Well, at least they're excited</i>
<i>But they don't understand

293
00:24:25.047 --> 00:24:27.508
<i>That special kind of feeling

294
00:24:27.591 --> 00:24:30.177
<i>In Christmas land

295
00:24:30.260 --> 00:24:32.930
Oh, well.

296
00:25:05.754 --> 00:25:10.134
There's got to be a logical way
to explain this Christmas thing.

297
00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:27.026
You've poisoned me for the last time,
you wretched girl!

298
00:25:35.576 --> 00:25:38.996
Oh, my head!

299
00:25:42.166 --> 00:25:44.877
The door is open!

300
00:25:45.627 --> 00:25:48.922
- Hello?
- Jack Skellington!

301
00:25:49.006 --> 00:25:51.425
Up here, my boy!

302
00:25:51.508 --> 00:25:54.636
Doctor, I need
to borrow some equipment.

303
00:25:54.720 --> 00:25:58.390
Is that so? Whatever for?

304
00:25:58.474 --> 00:26:01.935
I'm conducting a series of experiments.

305
00:26:02.019 --> 00:26:04.980
How perfectly marvelous!

306
00:26:05.064 --> 00:26:09.485
- Curiosity killed the cat, you know.
- I know.

307
00:26:09.568 --> 00:26:13.739
Come on into the lab
and we'll get you all fixed up.

308
00:26:14.865 --> 00:26:16.533
Experiments?

309
00:26:19.620 --> 00:26:22.122
Zero! I'm home!

310
00:27:26.311 --> 00:27:31.066
Interesting reaction,
but what does it mean?

311
00:29:10.249 --> 00:29:14.962
You can come out now
if you promise to behave.

312
00:29:15.504 --> 00:29:17.256
Sally?

313
00:29:17.965 --> 00:29:20.550
Sally!

314
00:29:20.634 --> 00:29:23.762
Gone again!

315
00:30:51.767 --> 00:30:55.604
<i>Something's up with Jack</i>
<i>Something's up with Jack

316
00:30:57.439 --> 00:31:00.776
<i>Don't know if we're ever</i>
<i>going to get him back

317
00:31:02.569 --> 00:31:05.572
<i>He's all alone up there</i>
<i>Locked away inside

318
00:31:08.116 --> 00:31:11.078
<i>- Never says a word</i>
<i>- Hope he hasn't died

319
00:31:11.161 --> 00:31:14.289
<i>Something's up with Jack</i>
<i>Something's up with Jack

320
00:31:22.214 --> 00:31:25.258
<i>Christmas time is buzzing in my skull

321
00:31:25.342 --> 00:31:28.470
<i>Will it let me be?</i>
<i>I cannot tell

322
00:31:28.553 --> 00:31:31.765
<i>There're so many things I cannot grasp

323
00:31:31.848 --> 00:31:34.810
<i>When I think I've got it</i>
<i>Then at last

324
00:31:34.893 --> 00:31:37.979
<i>Through my bony fingers it does slip

325
00:31:38.063 --> 00:31:40.190
<i>Like a snowflake in a fiery grip

326
00:31:40.273 --> 00:31:44.152
<i>Something here I'm not quite getting</i>
<i>Though I try, I keep forgetting

327
00:31:44.236 --> 00:31:47.989
<i>Like a memory long since past

328
00:31:48.073 --> 00:31:52.577
<i>Here in an instant, gone in a flash</i>
<i>What does it mean? What does it mean?

329
00:31:53.495 --> 00:31:56.873
<i>In these little bric-a-brac</i>
<i>A secret's waiting to be cracked

330
00:31:56.957 --> 00:32:01.378
<i>These dolls and toys confuse me so</i>
<i>Confound it all, I love it though

331
00:32:01.461 --> 00:32:05.173
<i>Simple objects, nothing more</i>
<i>But something's hidden through a door

332
00:32:05.257 --> 00:32:08.885
<i>Though I do not have the key

333
00:32:08.969 --> 00:32:13.265
<i>Something's here I cannot see</i>
<i>What does it mean? What does it mean?

334
00:32:14.516 --> 00:32:16.351
<i>What does it mean?

335
00:32:21.648 --> 00:32:24.359
<i>I've read these Christmas books</i>
<i>so many times

336
00:32:24.443 --> 00:32:27.654
<i>I know the stories</i>
<i>and I know the rhymes

337
00:32:27.737 --> 00:32:30.532
<i>I know the Christmas carols all by heart

338
00:32:30.615 --> 00:32:33.869
<i>My skull's so full</i>
<i>It's tearing me apart

339
00:32:33.952 --> 00:32:37.038
<i>As often as I've read them</i>
<i>Something's wrong

340
00:32:37.122 --> 00:32:40.167
<i>So hard to put my bony finger on

341
00:32:40.250 --> 00:32:43.587
<i>Or perhaps it's really not as deep</i>
<i>as I've been led to think

342
00:32:43.670 --> 00:32:47.090
<i>Am I trying much too hard?

343
00:32:47.174 --> 00:32:50.886
<i>Of course, I've been too close to see</i>
<i>The answer's right in front of me

344
00:32:50.969 --> 00:32:54.306
<i>Right in front of me</i>
<i>It's simple, really, very clear

345
00:32:54.389 --> 00:32:56.183
<i>Like music drifting in the air

346
00:32:56.266 --> 00:32:59.644
<i>Invisible, but everywhere

347
00:32:59.728 --> 00:33:03.690
<i>Just because I cannot see it</i>
<i>doesn't mean I can't believe it

348
00:33:03.773 --> 00:33:07.861
<i>You know, I think this Christmas thing</i>
<i>is not as tricky as it seems

349
00:33:07.944 --> 00:33:11.448
<i>And why should they have all the fun?</i>
<i>It should belong to anyone

350
00:33:11.531 --> 00:33:15.118
<i>Not anyone, in fact, but me</i>
<i>Why, I could make a Christmas tree

351
00:33:15.202 --> 00:33:18.747
<i>And there's no reason I can find</i>
<i>I couldn't handle Christmas time

352
00:33:18.830 --> 00:33:24.294
<i>I bet I could improve it, too</i>
<i>and that's exactly what I'll do

353
00:33:27.088 --> 00:33:28.590
Eureka!

354
00:33:28.673 --> 00:33:33.470
This year, Christmas will be ours!

355
00:33:37.599 --> 00:33:39.726
Patience, everyone.

356
00:33:39.809 --> 00:33:43.480
Jack has a special job for each of you.

357
00:33:44.981 --> 00:33:47.734
Dr. Finkelstein!

358
00:33:48.568 --> 00:33:51.571
Your Christmas assignment is ready.

359
00:33:53.740 --> 00:33:58.161
Dr. Finkelstein
to the front of the line!

360
00:34:02.123 --> 00:34:05.585
What kind of noise is that
for a baby to make?

361
00:34:05.669 --> 00:34:08.463
- Perhaps it can be improved?
- No problem!

362
00:34:08.547 --> 00:34:10.173
I knew it!

363
00:34:10.257 --> 00:34:13.260
Doctor, thank you for coming.

364
00:34:13.343 --> 00:34:16.054
We need some of these.

365
00:34:18.807 --> 00:34:22.602
Their construction should be
exceedingly simple, I think.

366
00:34:22.686 --> 00:34:25.730
How horrible our Christmas will be.

367
00:34:25.814 --> 00:34:28.817
No. How jolly!

368
00:34:28.900 --> 00:34:32.988
Oh, how jolly our Christmas will be.

369
00:34:35.740 --> 00:34:38.660
- What are you doing here?
- Jack sent for us.

370
00:34:38.743 --> 00:34:40.745
- Specifically.
- By name.

371
00:34:40.829 --> 00:34:41.997
- Lock.
- Shock.

372
00:34:42.080 --> 00:34:43.665
Barrel.

373
00:34:43.748 --> 00:34:48.587
Jack. Jack!
It's Boogie's boys.

374
00:34:48.670 --> 00:34:52.132
Halloween's finest trick-or-treaters!

375
00:34:52.215 --> 00:34:55.677
The job I have for you is top secret.

376
00:34:55.760 --> 00:34:58.763
It requires craft, cunning, mischief.

377
00:34:58.847 --> 00:35:02.183
And we thought you
didn't like us, Jack!

378
00:35:03.852 --> 00:35:07.188
Absolutely no one is to know about it.
Not a soul.

379
00:35:07.272 --> 00:35:09.691
Now, you must go to the forest.

380
00:35:09.774 --> 00:35:12.485
In the forest you will see a tree.

381
00:35:14.613 --> 00:35:16.364
… Christmas Town.

382
00:35:21.036 --> 00:35:23.204
And one more thing.

383
00:35:23.288 --> 00:35:27.083
Leave that no account
Oogie Boogie out of this!

384
00:35:27.167 --> 00:35:28.793
Whatever you say, Jack.

385
00:35:28.877 --> 00:35:31.546
- Of course, Jack.
- Wouldn't dream of it, Jack.

386
00:35:51.024 --> 00:35:53.777
<i>Kidnap Mr. Sandy Claws?

387
00:35:54.694 --> 00:35:57.447
<i>- I wanna do it</i>
<i>- Let's draw straws

388
00:35:58.281 --> 00:36:00.992
<i>- Jack said we should work together</i>
<i>- Three of a kind

389
00:36:01.076 --> 00:36:03.912
<i>- Birds of a feather</i>
<i>- Now and for ever

390
00:36:09.751 --> 00:36:13.004
<i>Kidnap the Sandy Claws</i>
<i>Lock him up real tight

391
00:36:13.088 --> 00:36:16.633
<i>Throw away the key</i>
<i>and then turn off all the lights

392
00:36:16.716 --> 00:36:20.220
<i>First we're going to set some bait</i>
<i>inside a nasty trap and wait

393
00:36:20.303 --> 00:36:23.765
<i>When he comes a-sniffing, we will</i>
<i>snap the trap and close the gate

394
00:36:23.848 --> 00:36:27.185
<i>Wait, I've got a better plan</i>
<i>to catch this big red lobster man

395
00:36:27.268 --> 00:36:30.397
<i>Pop him in a boiling pot</i>
<i>and when he's done, we'll butter him up

396
00:36:30.480 --> 00:36:34.234
<i>Kidnap the Sandy Claws</i>
<i>Throw him in a box

397
00:36:34.317 --> 00:36:37.862
<i>Bury him for 90 years</i>
<i>Then see if he talks

398
00:36:39.322 --> 00:36:42.075
<i>Then Mr. Oogie Boogie Man

399
00:36:42.867 --> 00:36:45.245
<i>Can take the whole thing over then

400
00:36:46.329 --> 00:36:48.790
<i>He'll be so pleased, I do declare

401
00:36:49.666 --> 00:36:52.168
<i>That he will cook him rare

402
00:36:58.967 --> 00:37:02.220
<i>I say that we take a cannon</i>
<i>Aim it at his door and then

403
00:37:02.303 --> 00:37:06.057
<i>Knock three times, and when he answers</i>
<i>Sandy Claws will be no more

404
00:37:06.141 --> 00:37:09.310
<i>You're so stupid, think now</i>
<i>If we blow him up to smithereens

405
00:37:09.394 --> 00:37:12.939
<i>We may lose some pieces and then</i>
<i>Jack will beat us black and green

406
00:37:13.022 --> 00:37:16.192
<i>Kidnap the Sandy Claws</i>
<i>Tie him in a bag

407
00:37:16.276 --> 00:37:19.404
<i>Throw him in the ocean</i>
<i>Then see if he is sad

408
00:37:19.487 --> 00:37:22.991
<i>Because Mr. Oogie Boogie</i>
<i>is the meanest guy around

409
00:37:23.074 --> 00:37:28.329
<i>If I were on his boogie list</i>
<i>I'd get out of town

410
00:37:29.956 --> 00:37:32.459
<i>He'll be so pleased by our success

411
00:37:33.668 --> 00:37:36.296
<i>That he'll reward us, too, I'll bet

412
00:37:37.172 --> 00:37:39.257
<i>Perhaps he'll make his special brew

413
00:37:40.508 --> 00:37:42.302
<i>Of snake and spider stew

414
00:37:42.385 --> 00:37:46.014
<i>We're his little henchmen</i>
<i>and we take our job with pride

415
00:37:46.097 --> 00:37:49.350
<i>We do our best to please him</i>
<i>and stay on his good side

416
00:37:49.434 --> 00:37:51.227
<i>I wish my cohorts weren't so dumb

417
00:37:51.311 --> 00:37:53.104
<i>- I'm not the dumb one</i>
<i>- You're no fun

418
00:37:53.188 --> 00:37:54.189
- Shut up!
- Make me.

419
00:37:54.272 --> 00:37:57.400
<i>I've got something, listen</i>
<i>This one is real good, you'll see

420
00:37:57.484 --> 00:38:01.112
<i>We'll send a present to his door</i>
<i>Upon there'll be a note to read

421
00:38:01.196 --> 00:38:04.365
<i>Now in the box we'll wait and hide</i>
<i>until his curiosity

422
00:38:04.449 --> 00:38:07.744
<i>Entices him to look inside</i>
<i>and then we'll have him one, two, three

423
00:38:07.827 --> 00:38:11.539
<i>Kidnap the Sandy Claws</i>
<i>Beat him with a stick

424
00:38:11.623 --> 00:38:14.751
<i>Lock him up for 90 years</i>
<i>See what makes him tick

425
00:38:14.834 --> 00:38:18.463
<i>Kidnap the Sandy Claws</i>
<i>Chop him into bits

426
00:38:18.546 --> 00:38:22.008
<i>Mr. Oogie Boogie</i>
<i>is sure to get his kicks

427
00:38:22.091 --> 00:38:25.678
<i>Kidnap the Sandy Claws</i>
<i>See what we will see

428
00:38:25.762 --> 00:38:30.475
<i>Lock him in a cage</i>
<i>and then throw away the key

429
00:38:35.688 --> 00:38:38.900
Sandy Claws, huh?

430
00:38:45.740 --> 00:38:48.743
It goes something like this.

431
00:38:53.414 --> 00:38:55.500
How about it?
Think you can you manage?

432
00:38:55.583 --> 00:38:58.920
A-one and a-two and a-three and …

433
00:39:05.718 --> 00:39:08.888
- Next!
- Fantastic!

434
00:39:08.972 --> 00:39:12.892
Now, why don't you all practice on that
and we'll be in great shape!

435
00:39:12.976 --> 00:39:16.271
Sally, I need your help
more than anyone's.

436
00:39:16.354 --> 00:39:19.691
You certainly do, Jack.
I had the most terrible vision.

437
00:39:19.774 --> 00:39:23.111
- That's splendid!
- No. It was about your Christmas.

438
00:39:23.194 --> 00:39:27.407
- There was smoke and fire!
- That's not my Christmas.

439
00:39:27.490 --> 00:39:31.160
My Christmas is filled
with laughter and joy,

440
00:39:31.244 --> 00:39:33.079
and this!

441
00:39:33.162 --> 00:39:36.916
My Sandy Claws outfit.
I want you to make it.

442
00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:40.503
Jack, please listen to me.
It's going to be a disaster!

443
00:39:40.587 --> 00:39:43.673
How could it be?
Just follow the pattern.

444
00:39:43.756 --> 00:39:46.050
