any naughty children this year.

511
00:45:33.105 --> 00:45:35.024
Now, who could that be?

512
00:45:37.902 --> 00:45:39.737
Trick or treat!

513
00:45:44.283 --> 00:45:47.828
You don't look like yourself, Jack.
Not at all!

514
00:45:47.912 --> 00:45:50.957
Isn't that wonderful?
It couldn't be more wonderful!

515
00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:53.459
But you're the Pumpkin King.

516
00:45:53.542 --> 00:45:58.047
Not anymore!
I feel so much better now!

517
00:45:58.130 --> 00:46:02.093
Jack, I know you think
something's missing, but …

518
00:46:02.176 --> 00:46:04.011
Sorry.

519
00:46:04.095 --> 00:46:06.806
You're right. Something is missing.

520
00:46:06.889 --> 00:46:10.935
But what?
I've got the beard, the coat,

521
00:46:11.018 --> 00:46:12.561
the boots, the belt …

522
00:46:12.645 --> 00:46:17.191
- Jack! This time we bagged him!
- This time we really did!

523
00:46:17.275 --> 00:46:20.319
- He sure is big, Jack.
- And heavy!

524
00:46:20.403 --> 00:46:21.946
Let me out!

525
00:46:22.863 --> 00:46:26.033
Sandy Claws. In person.

526
00:46:26.117 --> 00:46:27.910
What a pleasure to meet you!

527
00:46:29.370 --> 00:46:33.666
Why, you have hands.
You don't have claws at all!

528
00:46:35.167 --> 00:46:38.546
- Where am I?
- Surprised, aren't you?

529
00:46:38.629 --> 00:46:40.131
I knew you would be.

530
00:46:40.214 --> 00:46:43.759
You don't need to have another worry
about Christmas this year.

531
00:46:43.843 --> 00:46:46.929
- What?
- Consider this a vacation, Sandy.

532
00:46:47.013 --> 00:46:49.724
A reward.
It's your turn to take it easy.

533
00:46:49.807 --> 00:46:53.561
- But there must be some mistake.
- See that he's comfortable.

534
00:46:53.644 --> 00:46:57.315
Just a second, fellas. Of course!

535
00:46:57.398 --> 00:47:00.067
- That's what I'm missing. Thanks.
- But …

536
00:47:00.151 --> 00:47:01.736
You just can't …

537
00:47:01.819 --> 00:47:04.363
Hold on! Where are we going now?

538
00:47:04.447 --> 00:47:07.033
Oh, ho, ho! No …

539
00:47:07.116 --> 00:47:11.203
This is worse than I thought.
Much worse.

540
00:47:11.287 --> 00:47:13.289
I know!

541
00:47:13.372 --> 00:47:16.459
Me on vacation?
On Christmas Eve?!

542
00:47:16.542 --> 00:47:20.421
- Where are we taking him?
- To Oogie Boogie, of course.

543
00:47:20.504 --> 00:47:23.591
There isn't anywhere
more comfortable than that.

544
00:47:23.674 --> 00:47:28.220
- Jack said to make him comfortable.
- Yes, he did.

545
00:47:28.304 --> 00:47:32.683
Haven't you heard of peace on earth
and goodwill toward men?

546
00:47:32.767 --> 00:47:34.435
No!

547
00:47:42.443 --> 00:47:44.862
This will stop Jack!

548
00:47:56.123 --> 00:48:00.961
What a joy to think
of all we'll have in common!

549
00:48:01.045 --> 00:48:03.756
We'll have conversations

550
00:48:03.839 --> 00:48:06.717
worth having!

551
00:48:10.971 --> 00:48:12.973
Don't do this!

552
00:48:13.057 --> 00:48:15.726
Naughty children never get any presents.

553
00:48:15.810 --> 00:48:18.270
I think he might be too big!

554
00:48:19.063 --> 00:48:20.314
No, he's not.

555
00:48:20.398 --> 00:48:25.736
If he can go down a chimney,
he can fit down here!

556
00:48:53.639 --> 00:48:57.560
<i>Well, well, well</i>
<i>What have we here?

557
00:48:57.643 --> 00:49:02.356
<i>Sandy Claws, huh?</i>
<i>I'm really scared

558
00:49:02.440 --> 00:49:06.569
<i>So you're the one</i>
<i>everybody's talkin' about

559
00:49:06.652 --> 00:49:10.823
<i>You're jokin', you're jokin'</i>
<i>I can't believe my eyes

560
00:49:10.906 --> 00:49:15.244
<i>You're jokin' me, you gotta be</i>
<i>This can't be the right guy

561
00:49:15.327 --> 00:49:19.665
<i>He's ancient, he's ugly</i>
<i>I don't know which is worse

562
00:49:19.748 --> 00:49:24.170
<i>I might just split a seam now</i>
<i>if I don't die laughin' first

563
00:49:24.253 --> 00:49:28.466
<i>Mr. Oogie Boogie says</i>
<i>There's trouble close at hand

564
00:49:28.549 --> 00:49:32.678
<i>You'd better pay attention now</i>
<i>'cause I'm the Boogie Man

565
00:49:32.761 --> 00:49:37.266
<i>And if you aren't shakin'</i>
<i>There's somethin' very wrong

566
00:49:37.349 --> 00:49:41.228
<i>'Cause this may be the last time</i>
<i>You hear the Boogie song

567
00:49:47.651 --> 00:49:50.488
<i>I'm the Oogie Boogie Man

568
00:49:50.571 --> 00:49:55.075
<i>Release me now or you must face</i>
<i>the dire consequences

569
00:49:55.159 --> 00:49:59.538
<i>The children are expecting me</i>
<i>So please come to your senses

570
00:49:59.622 --> 00:50:03.751
<i>You're jokin', you're jokin'</i>
<i>I can't believe my ears

571
00:50:03.834 --> 00:50:08.088
<i>Would someone shut this fella up?</i>
<i>I'm drownin' in my tears

572
00:50:08.172 --> 00:50:12.593
<i>It's funny, I'm laughin'</i>
<i>You really are too much

573
00:50:12.676 --> 00:50:17.264
<i>And now, with your permission</i>
<i>I'm going to do my stuff

574
00:50:17.348 --> 00:50:20.476
- What are you going to do?
- The best I can.

575
00:50:22.436 --> 00:50:26.565
<i>The sound of rollin' dice to me</i>
<i>is music in the air

576
00:50:26.649 --> 00:50:30.945
<i>'Cause I'm a gamblin' Boogie Man</i>
<i>Although I don't play fair

577
00:50:31.028 --> 00:50:35.574
<i>It's much more fun, I must confess</i>
<i>when lives are on the line

578
00:50:35.658 --> 00:50:40.162
<i>Not mine, of course, but yours, old boy</i>
<i>Now, that'd be just fine

579
00:50:40.246 --> 00:50:44.667
<i>Release me fast or you will have</i>
<i>to answer for this heinous act

580
00:50:44.750 --> 00:50:48.629
<i>Oh, brother, you're something</i>
<i>You put me in a spin

581
00:50:48.712 --> 00:50:52.967
<i>You aren't comprehending</i>
<i>the position that you're in

582
00:50:53.050 --> 00:50:57.429
<i>It's hopeless, you're finished</i>
<i>You haven't got a prayer

583
00:50:57.513 --> 00:50:59.807
<i>'Cause I'm Mr. Oogie Boogie

584
00:50:59.890 --> 00:51:03.644
<i>And you ain't goin' nowhere

585
00:51:40.723 --> 00:51:45.144
Think of us as you soar
triumphantly through the sky,

586
00:51:45.227 --> 00:51:48.188
