of the … living!

593
00:52:08.459 --> 00:52:12.212
Oh, no. We can't take off in this.

594
00:52:12.296 --> 00:52:15.215
The reindeer can't see an inch
in front of their noses.

595
00:52:16.216 --> 00:52:19.094
This fog's as thick as …

596
00:52:19.178 --> 00:52:22.056
- Jellied brains.
- Or thicker!

597
00:52:22.139 --> 00:52:25.434
There go all of my hopes,

598
00:52:25.517 --> 00:52:27.645
my precious plans,

599
00:52:27.728 --> 00:52:29.438
my glorious dreams.

600
00:52:29.521 --> 00:52:33.025
There goes Christmas.

601
00:52:34.735 --> 00:52:38.072
No, Zero. Down, boy.

602
00:52:38.155 --> 00:52:42.076
My, what a brilliant nose you have.

603
00:52:42.159 --> 00:52:44.536
The better to light my way!

604
00:52:44.620 --> 00:52:46.914
To the head of the team, Zero.

605
00:52:48.874 --> 00:52:50.668
We're off!

606
00:52:54.004 --> 00:52:56.048
Wait, Jack. No!

607
00:53:17.444 --> 00:53:19.571
Goodbye, Jack.

608
00:53:19.655 --> 00:53:22.491
My dearest Jack.

609
00:53:22.574 --> 00:53:26.328
Oh, how I hope my premonition is wrong.

610
00:53:31.625 --> 00:53:36.880
<i>I sense there's something in the wind

611
00:53:36.964 --> 00:53:42.302
<i>That feels like tragedy's at hand

612
00:53:42.386 --> 00:53:47.474
<i>And though I'd like to stand by him

613
00:53:47.558 --> 00:53:52.479
<i>Can't shake this feeling that I have

614
00:53:52.563 --> 00:53:58.277
<i>The worst is just around the bend

615
00:53:58.360 --> 00:54:02.489
<i>And does he notice

616
00:54:02.573 --> 00:54:06.326
<i>My feelings for him?

617
00:54:06.410 --> 00:54:10.122
<i>And will he see

618
00:54:10.205 --> 00:54:14.460
<i>How much he means to me?

619
00:54:14.543 --> 00:54:19.423
<i>I think it's not to be

620
00:54:19.506 --> 00:54:25.179
<i>What will become</i>
<i>of my dear friend?

621
00:54:25.262 --> 00:54:29.975
<i>Where will his actions lead us then?

622
00:54:30.058 --> 00:54:35.647
<i>Although I'd like to join the crowd

623
00:54:35.731 --> 00:54:41.028
<i>In their enthusiastic cloud

624
00:54:41.111 --> 00:54:46.033
<i>Try as I may, it doesn't last

625
00:54:46.116 --> 00:54:50.954
<i>And will we ever

626
00:54:51.038 --> 00:54:55.167
<i>End up together?

627
00:54:55.250 --> 00:54:58.378
<i>No, I think not

628
00:54:58.462 --> 00:55:02.633
<i>It's never to become

629
00:55:02.716 --> 00:55:07.763
<i>For I am not the one

630
00:55:40.921 --> 00:55:42.256
Santa!

631
00:56:02.526 --> 00:56:04.444
Santa?

632
00:56:05.445 --> 00:56:06.905
Merry Christmas!

633
00:56:06.989 --> 00:56:09.616
And what is your name?

634
00:56:11.118 --> 00:56:15.581
That's all right. I have
a special present for you anyway.

635
00:56:15.664 --> 00:56:17.749
There you go, sonny.

636
00:56:26.800 --> 00:56:29.303
And what did Santa bring you, honey?

637
00:56:31.638 --> 00:56:34.892
Merry Christmas!

638
00:56:36.727 --> 00:56:38.729
Hello. Police.

639
00:56:39.688 --> 00:56:42.316
Attacked by Christmas toys?
That's strange.

640
00:56:42.399 --> 00:56:44.610
That's the second
toy complaint we've had.

641
00:57:28.320 --> 00:57:31.073
Mom! Dad! Help!

642
00:58:07.109 --> 00:58:11.613
You're welcome, one and all!

643
00:58:11.697 --> 00:58:13.865
Where'd you spot him?
Fast as we can, ma'am.

644
00:58:13.949 --> 00:58:16.076
Police. I know. A skeleton.

645
00:58:16.159 --> 00:58:20.330
Keep calm. Turn off the lights. Make
sure doors are locked. Hello. Police.

646
00:58:20.414 --> 00:58:22.874
Reports are pouring in
from all over the globe

647
00:58:22.958 --> 00:58:26.211
<i>that an impostor is shamelessly</i>
<i>impersonating Santa Claus,

648
00:58:26.294 --> 00:58:30.215
<i>mocking and mangling</i>
<i>this joyous holiday.

649
00:58:30.298 --> 00:58:34.136
<i>Authorities assure us that, at this</i>
<i>moment, military units are mobilizing

650
00:58:34.219 --> 00:58:37.180
<i>to stop the perpetrator</i>
<i>of this heinous crime.

651
00:58:37.264 --> 00:58:40.267
Jack. Someone has to help Jack!

652
00:58:40.350 --> 00:58:44.396
- Where did they take that Sandy Claws?
<i>- … come back and save Christmas.

653
